ce:section.ce:para:
The adsorption efficiency and adsorption capacity for Hg2+ ions were evaluated for FMCAB dose in the range between and 2.5 mg/L and 12.5 g/L, at randomly large contact time of 1 h. The percentage removal of Hg2+ increased exponentially for adsorbent dose of 7.5 g/L and was saturated for the batch of adsorbent dose of 12.5 g/L and the corresponding values of % removal was 66.60 % and 68.20 % respectively (

                           Fig. 7
                           ). This enhancement in Hg2+ adsorption is attributed to increase in active surface site on FMCAB adsorbent allowing a better adsorbate-adsorbent interaction. Further Hg2+ adsorption was studied using 7.5 g/L of adsorbent dose.
